  const sanitizedUsers = users.map(({ id, name }) => ({ id, name }));
  res.json(sanitizedUsers);
});
```

### 6. No CORS Configuration (OWASP A05: Security Misconfiguration)

Without explicit CORS configuration, the browser's same-origin policy applies — but if CORS is ever needed, the common mistake is to allow `*`. It's better to set it up restrictively now.

**Recommendation:**

```js
const cors = require('cors');

app.use(cors({
  origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGINS?.split(',') || ['https://yourdomain.com'],
  methods: ['GET'],
  allowedHeaders: ['Content-Type', 'Authorization'],
}));
```

---

## 🟡 Medium Issues

### 7. Hardcoded Port / No Environment Configuration (OWASP A05: Security Misconfiguration)

Port 3000 is hardcoded. In production, this should be configurable. Additionally, the app has no distinction between development and production modes.

**Recommendation:**

```js
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;

if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production') {
